            <h4>The problem</h4>
            <p>In the winter of 2020, the membership will be launched in a country where email usage is very low, and
                social sign up is preferred
                (I won't reveal details or show designs as the launch is still confidential).</p>
            <h4>Understand the market and the platform</h4>
            <p>I did some reading to understand the market better.
                And we met with our colleagues in that market to share knowledge and build a closer
                relationship.</p>
            <h4>Discuss technical limitations and draw up user flows</h4>
            <p>I worked closely with our IT Architect and Developers to understand technical limitations
                and draw up user flows where all scenarios are accounted for.
                I had to make assumptions about
                what would be the most user-friendly solutions, but was hoping to be able to test those soon.
            </p>
            <h4>Sketch, Design Review, Prototype</h4>
            <p>I sketched out different ideas for a layout to accommodate extra sign up options. I selected three
                thanks to feedback received in Design Review, then prepared prototypes for user test.</p>
            <h4>Test and Adjust</h4>
            <p>In user testing, I observed that one layout resulted in less errors than the others. However, no clear
                insights emerged around some of the tricky points in the journey, like signing up directly from the
                social
                media platform.

            </p>

